    <name>
				<text>1.5.2.12 Transposition</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise <br></p>
<p>Transpose, and then fully simplify, the given formulae to make the given variable the subject.</p>
<br>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>\({@eqn1@}\) for \(x\),  [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</li>
<li>\({@eqn2@}\) for \(x\),  [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</li>
<li>\({@eqn3@}\) for \(y\),  [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</li>
<li>\({@eqn4@}\) for \(x\),  [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>Adding {@a2@} to both sides of the equation gives: \[{@y+a2=a1*x@}\] We can then divide both sides of the equation by {@a1@} and simplify: \[{@x=y/a1+a2/a1@}\]</li>
<li>Subtracting {@a4*y@} from both sides of the equation gives: \[{@a1*x=a3-a4*y@}\] We can then divide both sides by {@a1@} giving: \[{@ta2@}\]</li>
<li>Subtracting{@a5*x@} from both sides of the equality gives: \[{@a1*y=a3-a5*x@}\] Then dividing both sides of the equation by {@a1@} gives: \[{@ta3@}\]</li>
<li>Adding {@a1*x@} to both sides of the equation gives: \[{@13-a2*y=a1*x@}\] Then dividing both sides of the equation by {@a1@} gives \[{@ta4@}\]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
